    "name": "StableCoin-MarketRisk-RateShock-100K-30d",
    "description": "ACTUS: MARKET RISK — T-BILL INTEREST RATE SHOCK ($100K Reserve)\n\nGAP ADDRESSED: §11.4 — Existing simulations assume fixed T-bill values.\nIn reality, interest rate changes affect T-bill mark-to-market values.\nA rate hike devalues existing T-bills, reducing backing ratio even\nthough no redemptions occurred.\n\nSCENARIO:\n  Day 1-10:  Fed funds rate stable at 5.0%\n  Day 11:    Rate hike to 5.5% (unexpected)\n  Effect:    T-bill MtM drops: $24,500 face → ~$24,200 market value\n             Aggregate reserve drops from $104,000 to $102,800\n             Backing ratio drops from 104% to 102.8%\n\nCombined with RedemptionPressure: does the market interpret rate shock\nas a risk signal? Does peg deviation increase?\n\nRegulatory context:\n  GENIUS Act requires WAM <= 93 days partly to mitigate rate risk.\n  Shorter-tenor T-bills have less interest rate sensitivity.\n\nContract: PAM representing stablecoin liability + rate-sensitive reserve\n\nOpen Postman Console (Ctrl+Alt+C) before running.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {"key": "actus_risk_host", "value": "localhost:8082"},
    {"key": "actus_sim_host", "value": "localhost:8083"}
  ],
